  'fixturesAndFittings.curtains_and_curtain_rails.bedroom_3': {
    sellerGuidance: `List every item in this category with complete accuracy and specificity. For fixtures (items attached to building that pass to buyer unless excluded), examples include: light fittings wired into ceiling or walls, fitted bathroom cabinets, fitted wardrobes or cupboards, shelving units fixed to walls, heated towel rails, thermostat controls, curtain poles or rails screwed to walls, fitted storage benches, and any electrical items built into the structure. For chattels (moveable goods that remain your property unless offered), examples include: freestanding furniture, loose rugs or carpets not glued down, table lamps, portable heaters, picture frames, books, artwork, and any items you can pick up and move. Be extremely specific in your descriptions: include brand names (e.g., "Smeg stainless steel integrated oven"), model numbers, colour, finish, and condition. For example, instead of "kitchen fittings - included," list: "Smeg integrated oven, stainless steel (included); integrated dishwasher Siemens (excluded); fitted kitchen units white melamine with handles (included)." For each item, clearly state: INCLUDED (buyer gets it), EXCLUDED (you are taking it or it is being removed), AVAILABLE BY SEPARATE NEGOTIATION (you will sell for additional agreed price), or NONE/NOT APPLICABLE. If an item is excluded and removal will leave visible damage or holes requiring repair, confirm whether you are responsible for making good. Any items listed as INCLUDED on the TA10 form become legally part of the sale contract and must remain in the property until completion; the buyer has a right to refuse completion if listed items are missing or have been damaged. Accuracy in this form prevents post-completion disputes and potential claims for breach of contract or misrepresentation. Take time to complete this thoroughly.`,
    buyerGuidance: `## What this means
The seller is confirming the window dressing status for Bedroom 3. Follow the same logic as other bedrooms: fitted items stay, loose hangings usually leave. What's being left affects the room's comfort and your first-night experience in the property.
## What a good answer looks like
A specific breakdown of what's left in the room -- e.g., "thermal roller blind fitted to frame (staying); linen curtains on pole (staying)" or "no window dressing (not included)". The answer should cover all windows in the room and clarify whether items are fixed or loose.
## Red flags
• Vague answers that don't match your viewing photos or notes
• High-value items like thermal or blackout blinds marked as "not included" when you saw them in place
• Damage or stains noted in photos but no mention of condition or removal responsibility in this answer
• Inconsistency between what the listing advertised and what the seller now says
• No answer given for a room where you clearly photographed window dressing Questions to ask
• If fitted blinds are staying, ask your surveyor whether they're in safe working order and tested
• Cross-check with your solicitor that the contract's fittings schedule matches this answer exactly
• If no window dressing is included, ask whether the windows need insulation or have exposure issues`,
    disclaimer: DISCLAIMER,
  },
